Html:
Hi Radioman,

I know you will not remember me but you may remember a few years ago I donated $80.00 US to you.

I used GMap.NET back then and everything worked great. But now I have a new challenge and I’m hoping you can help me.

I saw a demonstration of the Googles Map Engine two days ago: http://mapsengine.google.com and it was great.

The company I contract for has a paid Maps Engine account.

I need to pass Maps Engine our log-in information and a list of latitudes and longitudes from a Visual Studio C# project using their webBrowser.

If I cannot simply pass the locations list in the HTML then I need to know how to pass it a CSV file location.

But I’m not good at this and cannot figure out how to automate it (I searched the GMap.NET dicusssions).

Can GMap.NET handle this?

If not can you give me a short demonstration C# project which logs-in and gets the data?

I can pay you if it’s not something you can put together quickly. Just let me know.

Thanks again,

Dennis Vogel

Mobile, AL USA
